      <div xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988">
        <head xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-Hd1e99" type="question-title">De solicitudine</head>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-d1e102">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e45988-Qd1e112" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-Rd1e104">Gregorius, in <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-Qd1e112">Sancti viri, quia brevitatem vitae desinenter
              aspiciunt, quasi quotidie morientes vivunt; et tanto se sollicitius mansuris
              praeparant, quanto et nulla esse transitoria ex fine semper pensant.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-d1e117">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e45988-Qd1e127" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-Rd1e119">Gregorius, in <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-Qd1e127">Mens tanto altius inter tentationum fluctus
              attollitur, quanto sollicitius ab hujus saeculi cogitatione vacuatur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-d1e132">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e45988-Qd1e142" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-Rd1e134">Gregorius, in <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-Qd1e142">Magna sollicitudine ad curam nostrae
              meliorationis accingimur, quando id virtutis in aliis cernimus, quod non
              habemus.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-d1e147">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e45988-Qd1e157" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-Rd1e149">Gregorius, in <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-Qd1e157">Illa sollicitudo praepositorum utilis est,
              cautela laudabilis, in qua totum ratio agit, et furor sibi nil vindicat.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-d1e163">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e45988-Qd1e173" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-Rd1e165">Gregorius, in <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-Qd1e173">Quanto morti vicinior efficeris, tanto fieri
              sollicitior atque timidior debes.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-d1e178">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e45988-Qd1e188" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-Rd1e180">Gregorius, in <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-Qd1e188">Cum honoris augmento, cura quoque sollicitudinis
              debet excrescere.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-d1e193">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e45988-Qd1e203" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-Rd1e195">Gregorius, in <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-Qd1e203">Cum cuncta negotia sollicitudine indagandae
              veritatis indigeant, tamen quae ad dejectionem sacerdotalium graduum spectant, sunt
              districtius trutinanda.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-d1e208">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e45988-Qd1e218" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-Rd1e210">Joannes Chrysostomus, <title>super Matthaeum</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-Qd1e218">Occupatio virilium solicitudinum, suggestionum
              voluptates plerumque excludit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-d1e223">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e45988-Qd1e233" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-Rd1e225">Bernardus, <title>super Cantica</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-Qd1e233">Omnis cura sanctorum, spreto ornatu cultuque
              superfluo exterioris sui hominis, qui certe corrumpitur, omni se diligentia praebet,
              et occupat excolendo, atque decorando interiori illi, qui ad imaginem Dei est, et
              renovatur de die in diem.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-d1e238">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e45988-Qd1e248" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-Rd1e240">Bernardus, in <title>Sermonibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-Qd1e248">Dignum valde est, et omnino exigit ratio
              aequitatis, ut quibus a constitutione mundi regnum paratur, ipsi etiam sese regno
              parare non negligant.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-d1e254">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e45988-Qd1e264" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-Rd1e256">Augustinus, <title>de Ordine disciplinae</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-Qd1e264">Opera danda est optimis moribus; Deus enim
              noster aliter nos exaudire non poterit, bene autem viventes facillime
              exaudiet.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-d1e269">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e45988-Qd1e279" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-Rd1e271">Seneca, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e45988-Qd1e279">Perseverandum est, et assiduo studio robur
              addendum, donec bona mens sit quod bona voluntas est.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
